09/01/2008
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska's (RS) new President Rajko Kuzmanovic said on Tuesday (January 8th) that the constitutional order imposed by the Dayton Accords is best for BiH , and any other constitution would not be viable. He stressed that RS's priority should be to preserve its constitutional status, territorial integrity and equal status under those accords. He reiterated that any attempt to dismantle RS would fail. The entity is celebrating the Day of the Republic on Wednesday. (Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 09/01/08; PBS - 08/01/08)
